  position: fixed;
  // `right` (the horizontal pin) is set via inline style in JS — no CSS
  // horizontal transform needed here. Only translateY(-50%) for vertical
  // centering. The previous translate(calc(-100% - spacer), -50%) used
  // `-100%` of the element's own width to shift left, which is unstable for
  // a block-level fixed div without an explicit width (can resolve to
  // viewport width in some compositing paths). See FB-156.
