### Append to `docs/design-feedback-log.md`

```markdown
#### FB-157: "Active label on wrong side — right of rail, past viewport"

**UX Intent:** Active ScrollSpy label must join the left-side label gutter shared by all hover labels — right-edge aligned at `notch.left − 8px`, growing leftward.
**Root Cause:** The portaled `.highlightLabelAnchor` (a `position: fixed` block `div`) used `left: notch.left` + CSS `transform: translate(calc(-100% - spacer), -50%)`. The `-100%` in `translate` is a percentage of the **element's own rendered width**, not the notch width. A `position:fixed` block div without explicit `width` can resolve to viewport width in certain browser compositing paths (exacerbated by `will-change: top, left`). When it does, `translate(-100%)` = translate by one full viewport width, placing the label far off-screen or — in other paths — the transform composites against the raw `left` value and the label renders at `left: notch.left` with no effective leftward shift, putting it flush to the right of the rail and past the viewport. Changing the query from `.tick` to `[data-notch-index]` (the previous attempted fix) only shifted the `left` value by ~12px and could not address the self-width reference failure.
**Resolution:** Replaced `left + translate(-100%)` with CSS `right` positioning. JS now computes `right = window.innerWidth − notch.left + 8`. CSS `transform` reduced to `translateY(-50%)` only (vertical centering). The right edge is now pinned to `notch.left − 8px` regardless of label text width or element self-width — identical to the in-rail hover labels' `right: calc(100% + spacer)`. See FB-156 (original portal / AP-070 split fix).
**Pattern extracted → `design.md` §13 / `content-navigation.md` §13.5**
