## Principle

> **Never use `translate(-N%)` to offset a portal element into a gutter defined by a sibling's CSS `right` property.** The two percentage bases are different things — `right: calc(100% + gap)` on an absolutely-positioned child uses the *containing block's* width; `translate(-100%)` on a portal element uses the *portal element's own* width. They only agree when label-text width happens to equal the containing block width. Use CSS `right` (distance from viewport right edge) so both are anchored to the same fixed point: the notch's left edge in viewport space. (AP-070 / FB-156 / FB-157)
